There are 3 types of loops in Java.

	for loop
	while loop
	do-while loop





for loop  

for(int i=1;i<=10;i++){  
	System.out.println(i);  
} 



while loop

int i=1;  
while(i<=10){  
    System.out.println(i);  
	i++;  
}  


do-while loop

If you have to execute the loop at least once
The Java do-while loop is executed at least once because condition is checked after loop body.


int i=1;  
do{  
    System.out.println(i);  
	i++;  
}while(i<=10);  






